CanTho
TP.Description: Can Tho city is famous for its gentle river beauty, verdant orchards, and the generous and hospitable atmosphere of the western people, which has captivated tourists from near and far. Can Tho travel itinerary explores the land known as the "Western capital" with a cool fresh climate, bold Southern landscape, immense fields, interlaced canals, ancient houses and many rustic delicacies only found in the Southwest region.

TP.name: AnGiang
TP.Description: An Giang makes a strong impression on visitors by the idyllic beauty of the western region of the river, where there is a mixture and convergence of many unique cultures of the Kinh, Khmer, Cham, and Chinese communities. . Besides, An Giang also attracts many tourists by the charming natural scenery, poetic by the green rice fields, jaggery rows soaring to the sky. With the terrain of both plains and hills, the mysterious That Son mountain range, many historical and cultural relics and many impressive check-in points, An Giang is attracting a large number of tourists. Let's find out the super beautiful An Giang tourist destinations that must be visited:

TP.name: BacKan
TP.Description: Bac Kan is a province in the Northeast mountainous region of Vietnam. It borders Cao Bang, Lang Son, Tuyen Quang and Thai Nguyen provinces. With typical mountainous terrain, Bac Kan is home to 7 ethnic groups: Tay, Nung, Kinh, Dao, Mong, Hoa and San Chay. Among them, the Tay ethnic group has the largest number.

TP.name: BaRiaVungTau
TP.Description: Vung Tau is a coastal city in Ba Ria - Vung Tau province. Back Beach is the beach most often chosen by Vung Tau tourists to bathe. In addition, Vung Tau also has notable attractions such as the Statue of Christ the King on Small Mountain, Shakyamuni Buddha Temple and the White Palace located close to the sea. Nghinh Ong festival and Dinh Co festival are the two most prominent cultural festivals of Vung Tau.

TP.name: BacLieu
TP.Description: If you have the opportunity to visit the Southwest region, do not ignore Bac Lieu province. The land has long been famous for being rich and fertile. This is also the land of cultural convergence of three ethnic groups Kinh - Hoa - Khmer expressed through unique cultural works, creating their own beauty. Referring to Bac Lieu, people immediately think of Bac Lieu's son - a famous playboy once or the hometown of the late musician Cao Van Lau, who composed the famous "Da Co Hoai Lang" tune. Coming to Bac Lieu, visitors not only have the opportunity to visit the Bac Lieu prince's house but also have the opportunity to listen to the folk music performed by garden artists and discover many attractive destinations. Witnessing with your own eyes, you will be surprised by what nature favors this land. Please introduce the beautiful tourist destinations in Bac Lieu that must be visited.

TP.name: BacGiang
TP.Description: Bac Giang is a mountainous province with diverse topography, with both high mountains and midlands alternating with plains; The climate is relatively mild, less affected by storms, floods and droughts. Convenient transportation system with road, railway, waterway and near Noi Bai international airport.
